attempt to be successful. If the roll fails, the referee knows that the thief has been noticed and should determine enemies&rsquo; actions appropriately.</p>\n<h2><span id=\"After_Reaching_9th_Level\" class=\"mw-headline\">After Reaching 9th Level</span></h2>\n<p>A thief can establish a thief den, attracting 2d6 apprentices of 1st level. These thieves will serve the character with some reliability; however, should any be arrested or killed, the PC will not be able to attract apprentices to replace them. A successful thief might use these followers to start a Thieves&rsquo; Guild.</p>\n<h2><span id=\"Thief_Level_Progression\" class=\"mw-headline\">Thief Level Progression</span></h2>\n<table style=\"height: 272px; width: 95%; border-color: #444444; border-style: solid; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;\" border=\"1px\" cellspacing=\"0px\" cellpadding=\"8px\">\n<thead>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 8px; text-align: center; background-color: #696863; width: 2em; height: 17px;\" scope=\"col\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 8px; text-align: center; background-color: #696863; width: 6em; height: 17px;\" scope=\"col\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 8px; text-align: center; background-color: #696863; width: 5em; height: 17px;\" scope=\"col\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 8px; text-align: center; background-color: #696863; width: 4em; height: 17px;\" scope=\"col\">&nbsp;</td>\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 8px; text-align: center; background-color: #505050; width: 2em; height: 17px;\" colspan=\"5\" scope=\"col\"><strong>Saving Throws</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr style=\"height: 17px;\">\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 8px; text-align: center; background-color: #696863; width: 2em; height: 17px;\" scope=\"col\"><strong>Level</strong></td>\n<td style=\"border: none; padding: 8px; text-align: center; background-color: #696863; width: 6em; height: 17px;\" scope=\"col\"><strong>XP</s